    <Section>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleHeader1}">Be Smart! Don't Start Smoking!</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleHeader2}">by Jenna</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleBody}">
            Be smart and don't start to smoke.
            Did you know women who smoke have at least a 10 times greater likelihood of lung cancer than non-smoking women?
            Between 1960 and 1990, the death rate among women who smoke increased by more than 400%.
            Smoking by women in the United States is associated with almost as many deaths from heart disease as from deaths from lung cancer, more than 61,000 each year. 
            Each year, about 8,000 women die from strokes attributable to smoking.
            Look at all the things that could happen if you smoke.
            Before you start a deadly habit, stop smoking!
        </Paragraph>
    </Section>
    
    <Section>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleHeader1}">Smoking is Wrong</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleHeader2}">by Brandon</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleBody}">
            Smoking is very wrong. 
            It affects your heart, brain, bloodstream and other parts of your body. 
            It's possible to get diseases from smoking and you can even die.
            A lot of people these days are beginning to smoke.
            That's because they don't care what cigarettes do to their bodies.
            They think it makes them cool.
            Well, they're so wrong.
            Smoking can turn your lungs black and make it hard to breathe.
            You should make good choices. 
            Don't smoke, someone loves you.
        </Paragraph>
