    <Section>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleHeader1}">The Rings Around Planets</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleHeader2}">by Trevor</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleBody}">
            The rings around planets are very interesting.
            They are made of ice and meteors.
            Saturn has the largest ring system in our solar system.
            It is made up of over 20 different rings.
            Rings are usually around gassy planets.
            For example, Saturn and Jupiter are both gassy planets and both of those planets have rings.
            Also, rings are always around outer planets - for example, Uranus, Neptune, Jupiter and Saturn.
            The rings around planets are very interesting.
        </Paragraph>
    </Section>

