        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleHeader1}">No Fingerboards in School</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleHeader2}">by Stephanie</Paragraph>
        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource ParagraphArticleBody}">
            Students from Hammond Elementary School are being distracted by fingerboards when given directions by teachers. 
            It's all happening here at Hammond.
            I've done a survey on fingerboards in school.
            All the boys in my class say fingerboards should be allowed in class, with the exception of Morgan; he doesn't think they should.
            Our teacher thinks the toys shouldn't even be brought into school, and most of the other teachers do too.
            So kids what should we do?
        </Paragraph>
